					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">MMC5 supports CHR RAM, though no existing cart board came with CHR RAM. You'd have to modify a board to take CHR ROM, just as you'd have to modify cart boards to take flash memory for PRG ROM.<br /><br />Currently there's no CPLD clone of MMC5, so think about that if you're seeking cart manufacturing.<br /><br />For &quot;constant upload of data to video RAM&quot;, look at what's going on in <em>Haunted: Halloween '85</em>. The demo is part of the forthcoming <a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=200083#p200083" class="postlink">third volume of <em>Action 53</em></a>.</div>

