				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">That was one of the things that surprised me when I started looking into NES.<br /><br />Like flashing/changing one sprite's palette different colours to show damage states etc. seems like such a common / obvious / easy technique on most other systems I'm familiar with, but on NES when it happens it's usually designed very specially around it. Maybe having several versions of the sprite in CHR for different rotations of the colour, or reusing one of the existing palettes instead, or if it's a &quot;background&quot; sprite using attributes instead of changing the palette itself. I did not expect all these work-arounds before I got to know the NES.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

